This paper deals with the synthesis of optimal implementations for reactive systems, which involves the use of games with quantitative objectives. The paper focuses on the use of automata with lexicographic mean-payoff conditions to express quantitative properties, which suggests that it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the solution of lexicographic mean-payoff games and games with both lexicographic mean-payoff and parity objectives, which suggests that it may also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms for solving these novel graph games, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the synthesis of optimal implementations for reactive systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories.
